// Page HeroOrVigilante Text :
"P2090520223" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Noise Within Noise</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>While tuning your police band between two channels you hear something very unusual.<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>After adjusting the tuner on your police band radio you overhear something very odd, a series of short beeps and clicks being sent over the airwaves.  You manage to figure out the source and receiving end of the encrypted message, discovering that these messages are being sent from a nearby warehouse to a secret Longbow base in the vicinity.  Shortly after comparing the frequencies and techniques used to send encrypted messages you discover that the type of signal being sent out is very similar to one used by covert Arachnos operations.  Is it possible that Longbow has been infiltrated by Arachnos?  It is definitely worth investigating.</scale></color></font><br><br>You could head off to the source of the transmission and discover who is sending the messages.<br><br>Alternatively, you could investigate the Longbow base and find out if there is anything strange going on there."
// Answer Text :
"P555685432" "HERO: Investigate the source of the encrypted message."
// Answer Text :
"P4049074098" "VIGILANTE: Investigate the Longbow base and deal with any traitors."
// Page Rogue Text :
"P2154288114" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Noise Within Noise</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>While tuning your police band between two channels you hear something very unusual.<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>After adjusting the tuner on your police band radio you overhear something very odd, a series of short beeps and clicks being sent over the airwaves.  You manage to figure out the source and receiving end of the encrypted message, discovering that these messages are being sent from a nearby warehouse to a secret Longbow base in the vicinity.  Shortly after comparing the frequencies and techniques used to send encrypted messages you discover that the type of signal being sent out is very similar to one used by covert Arachnos operations.  Is it possible that Longbow has been infiltrated by Arachnos?  It is definitely worth investigating.</scale></color></font><br><br>You don't like the sound of this, you're aware of how far Arachnos' corruption reaches.  You could investigate the source of the transmission and ensure that there is no Arachnos activity going on there."
// Page UnableToInvestigate Text :
// Answer Text :
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


