// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - DialogTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page HeroOrVigilante Text :
"P3383750232" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>The Nemesis Meme</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You find a laptop on the ground, possibly belonging to whoever you just beat down. The internet browser is open on the laptop with the words, 'NEMESIS MEME FORUMS' displayed at the top. It seems various people in Paragon go here to joke about 'everything is a Nemesis plot', especially with the introduction of Architect Entertainment. However, one post by someone called McHackerSmith catches your eye...<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>Hey guys, I hope one of you can contact the proper authorities on this. Remember how I said that I was pretty sure the girl I was hitting on at work was a Nemesis automaton and you all laughed and said I was just ugly? Well it turns out she IS an automaton! I hacked her system earlier and found out the location of a warehouse where a bunch of them are made. I've got a link below to it.<br><br>Problem is...turns out most of my other 'co-workers' were automatons too. They've got the entire office held hostage! Look, I know it's bad, but these are my final words to the world. On a forum of all places, right? You guys need to get this info to a hero so they can take down that warehouse - there's only me and two other 'norms' here in the office. We'll give our lives to help stop Nemesis. You guys just need to make sure someone stops this!</scale></color></font><br><br>The automaton problem in Paragon seems to be growing worse by the day - though the fact that this man was able to discover one and hack its systems must mean he is no ordinary person. He did say to go after the warehouse where the automatons are being made...but there are lives at stake here. You have the power to go into that office and save that man's life. Maybe it would mean that Nemesis clears out of this warehouse, but you can always use the help of 'McHackerSmith' again in the future.<br><br>Though on the other hand...this could have all been a fluke. And he <i>is</i> willing to give his life for the greater good. Focusing on taking down that warehouse would mean much less automatons walking around the city - even if it's at the price of this man and his co-workers' lives. "
// Answer Text :
"P3864140379" "HERO: Save McHackerSmith and his co-workers!"
// Answer Text :
"P2119926325" "VIGILANTE: Destroy the Automaton warehouse!"
// Page Rogue Text :
"P2884908231" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>The Nemesis Meme</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You find a laptop on the ground, possibly belonging to whoever you just beat down. The internet browser is open on the laptop with the words, 'NEMESIS MEME FORUMS' displayed at the top. It seems various people in Paragon go here to joke about 'everything is a Nemesis plot', especially with the introduction of Architect Entertainment. However, one post by someone called McHackerSmith catches your eye...<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>Hey guys, I hope one of you can contact the proper authorities on this. Remember how I said that I was pretty sure the girl I was hitting on at work was a Nemesis automaton and you all laughed and said I was just ugly? Well it turns out she IS an automaton! I hacked her system earlier and found out the location of a warehouse where a bunch of them are made. I've got a link below to it.<br><br>Problem is...turns out most of my other 'co-workers' were automatons too. They've got the entire office held hostage! Look, I know it's bad, but these are my final words to the world. On a forum of all places, right? You guys need to get this info to a hero so they can take down that warehouse - there's only me and two other 'norms' here in the office. We'll give our lives to help stop Nemesis. You guys just need to make sure someone stops this!</scale></color></font><br><br>You know, at least the Rogue Isles don't have this rampant problem of Nemesis Automatons running about. Sure, there's Arachnos agents in most offices, and then the stray Malta or Crey base using an office as a cover up. But you don't have this widespread problem of people actually being <i>machines</i>. You almost feel bad for the people in Paragon. You don't really care too much about taking down this warehouse, but...there are normal people stuck in that office, being held up by the people they thought were their friends. Someone needs to help them - and it certainly won't be the JohnnyBlazeEm, the person who responded to McHackerSmith's post with a, 'LOL! can i have ur stuff?'"
// Page UnableToInvestigate Text :
// Answer Text :
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


